# INSTRUCTIONS:
# 1. Copy this file to .env:
#    cp .env.example .env
#
# 2. Fill in your actual credentials in .env
#
# 3. NEVER commit .env to Git (it's in .gitignore)

# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# UDL API CREDENTIALS
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Option 1: Use username + password (recommended for first-time setup)
UDL_USERNAME=your_username_here
UDL_PASSWORD=your_password_here

# Option 2: Use existing token (if you already have one)
# UDL_TOKEN=your_base64_token_here

# NOTE: If you provide UDL_TOKEN, it will be used directly.
#       If you provide UDL_USERNAME and UDL_PASSWORD, a token will be generated.
#       Don't provide both - choose one method.

